title: For Sale/Trade:  Diamondback .380 pocket pistol (GEN 1!!)
postcontent:
Up for sale, or trade, is a DiamondBack .380 acp pocket pistol. It is the difficult to find Gen 1. DB380 generation 2's were only made because Kahr sued DiamondBack for using their patented fire control design without permission, so Diamond Back was forced to use a new and unknown fire control system. Therefore, the Gen 1's are a superior, proven, and more reliable fire control group. The DB380's are also known as "micro glocks" for their looks and reliability  (Gen 1).

This DB380 has been consistently  reliable to me. It was my daily carry for almost a year. It comes with 3 magazines. One of the mags has a finger extension. It comes with the manual, the hard case, and 7 rounds of fmj (I prefer fmj for more penetration and feeding reliability). 

It is in excellent to superior condition. I would rate it an 8.5 It is very easy to conceal in any clothing. You can carry this 7 round powerhouse in shorts, dress pants, or jeans without a problem. Thank you for your interest.
